comment: 3rd place Minnesota BEER DABBLER.  Temp too high on this one (hit 154F)..keep @ 152F Sacch' and 65F Ferm.

BTW..this is my 1st recipe.  I'm not sure why Lactose is calculated as fermentable?  I'm sure I did something wrong.  It's calculated in the FG, but obviously it won't ferment.  This one should be right around 1.030, with an ABV around 5%...not even CLOSE to 6.8%
